{
  "texts": [
    "For compounds comprising multiple distinct fragments following this \"washing\" procedure, all but the fragment with the highest number of heavy atoms were discarded.",
    "Furthermore, molecules containing <3 or >100 heavy atoms, as well as radical species, were excluded from the data set.",
    "This procedure yielded a data set of 742 k unique SMILES-strings with annotated biologic affinity.",
    "Using a cut-off of a binding affinity of 200 nM, removing duplicates, a maximal SMILES-string length of 97 (using the longest SMILES-length from five randomized sampled SMILES-strings) for the ligand, and a minimum number of five ligands per target resulted in a drug-target graph consisting of 501 k unique binding affinities for 360 k unique ligands and 2989 unique target-IDs.",
    "Preprocessing PDBbind."
  ]
}